# Inversion of Control (IoC)

## Definition

Inversion of Control (IoC) is a design principle in which the responsibility of creating and managing objects is transferred from the programmer to the Spring IoC Container.

## Advantages

- Loose Coupling
- Better Maintainability
- Easy Testing
- Reusable Components
- Cleaner Code

## Key Point

Spring achieves IoC using Dependency Injection (DI).
